grep command
Searches (possibly using regular expressions) for specified text (parameter 1) within selected files (parameter 2).
i.e. head *.html
Above will search for text 'head' within all html files (i.e. those with an html suffix).

Can also search within a set of results passed to it via pipes redirecting output.
i.e. env | grep ^T
Above will search for all environmental variables that begin with capital letter T.
